<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Xyneth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm writin this post because my guild has a slight delima.  We have about 12 tanks and casters 40-51, which is a good mix of those.  But we only have one cleric, level 44, played by one of the tanks.  We're a nice, friendly group of people, but our raiding ability is hampered by our lack of clerics.  We've had some well played, nice clerics in the past, but they've all left.  Our guild isen't all about killing the best mob(for level 40-51   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif">), or doing the most events or anything, but if our one (1) cleric can't show up, we have no chance of doing some of the simplist things.  Even when our cleric can make it, we usualy end up all sticking together in one group(15 people at frenzy seems overkill) because we don't have the healing power.<P>So, my question to you is, what is a cleric in their 30's looking for in a guild?  What outward apearance should our guild have to attract the cleric class?  I say in there 30's because most clerics 40+ are already guilded.  Not that we don't want 40+ clerics, but it is easier and more bountiful to concentrate on the clerics in there 30's.  So, should we host certain raids where cleric armor/quests items drop?  If so, where?  Costs of reagents are always covered, above the normal loot split, so i don't think that is the problem.  Please, any advise you can give would be greatly appreciated!<P>Thanks<P>Xyneth~~<P>PS - I know there was a thread on this a few months ago, but that was directed towards the 50+ crowd.  If you could try to limit this to 30-40ish, I would greatly appreciat it.  Thanks!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ketocon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">tower of frozen shadow raids are nice .. loved going there in my 30s<P>having people in your level range to group with is a BIG +!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Grumbles</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If I were faced with needing to recruit a specific class, I would keep lists from pickup groups of clerics that were fun to group with and did the job well.  From there I would keep in contact with them, invites to xp groups, raids, guild parties and such.  <P>You might find a cleric right away that is looking for a guild to join you or you might get some return later but either way it's a good way to make some friends and if you stick with it you should meet enough wandering clerics that you'll have 5 to 10 that know you well enough to go hunting with you guys even if they are in another guild.<P>The best way to get someone to join your guild is let them spend some time with you and see how they fit in.  If they feel welcome, chances are good they're gonna look for you when they log in.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18964" TARGET=_blank>Grumbles</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bindol</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Grumbles:<BR><B>The best way to get someone to join your guild is let them spend some time with you and see how they fit in.  If they feel welcome, chances are good they're gonna look for you when they log in.<P></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Grumbles nailed it on the head.  We had a similar problem, with me being the only cleric in the guild for a while.  When I wasn't available, they ended up having to find other clerics to group with.  We now have 4 50+ clerics and one 49.<P>Bindol Stonehealer<BR>Vicar of Blackwing (Sol Ro)</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
